Eshowe Eshowe detectives have arrested a 23-year-old hitchhiker in connection with the murder of a school principal from that area. Colonel Thembeka Mbele said on Monday morning school principal, Busisiwe Nzuza, offered a lift to a hitchhiker from Empangeni towards Eshowe. &quot;While on the way near Nkwalini, the hitchhiker allegedly produced a firearm and demanded the vehicle from the principal,&quot; said Mbele. The 44-year-old principal was shot in the head and the assailant fled on foot. In a statement on Tuesday, police said they had arrested a suspect in connection with the murder. He will appear in the Eshowe Magistrate s Court on Thursday. Police have warned motorists against giving lifts to strangers. African News Agency